What does "arsenokoitai" really mean?"Nobody knows for certain."Arsenokoitai" is made up of two parts: "arsen" means "man"; "koitai" means "beds."Although the word in English Bibles is interpreted as referring to homosexuals, we can be fairly certain that this is not the meaning that Paul wanted to convey. If he had, he would have used the word "paiderasste." That was the standard Greek term at the time for sexual behavior between males. We can conclude that he probably meant something different than people who engaged in male-male adult sexual behavior.Many sources have speculated about the meaning of "arsenokoitai:..."   http://www.religioustolerance.org/homarsen.htm  